Fortress Investment Group LLC (FIG)  said
it hired David Shell to start a new growth equity business for
institutional investors at its Logan Circle Partners unit.  Shell previously was co-chief investment officer of the
growth equities investment team at Goldman Sachs Asset
Management, where he was responsible for about $20 billion in
client assets, New York-based Fortress said today in a
statement. The appointment of Shell, who will be based in Tampa,
 Florida , marks the addition of institutional equities at Logan
Circle, which manages about $21 billion across 15 fixed-income
strategies, Fortress said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
